ut healthcare costs, his posts reached fewer than 800,000 users. Most of his posts reach a minimum of 10 million users.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> While it&#39;s unclear what exactly is causing the drop in user reach, this wouldn&#39;t be the first time Elon Musk&#39;s X appeared to be affecting user engagement. In August, X <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/x-is-slowing-down-links-to-websites-elon-musk-has-publicly-feuded-with-185544463.html"><ins>was reported</ins></a> to be interfering with links to Mastodon, Bluesky, Threads, Substack and of course—the <em>New York Times</em> , to make them load noticeably slower. At the time, it appeared that the high-profile websites affected were only big names that Musk publicly attacked in the past.</p><p> X and The <em>New York Times</em> could not be immediately reached for comment.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/x-is-allegedly-limiting-user-reach-to-posts-that-link-to-the-new-york-times-224200207.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/x-is-allegedly-limiting-user-reach-to-posts-that-link-to-the-new-york-times-224200207.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7cf49370-2c96-4085-8c64-566b28196ad3</guid><dc:creator>马拉克·萨利赫</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 11 Sep 2023 22:42:00 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694472122</ingested><modified> 2023-09-11T22:42:08+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Malak Saleh]]></category><media:content height="2452" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-